    <p><strong>Sweet making machine prices in India in 2026 range from ₹5,000 for a basic kulfi mould set to over ₹5,00,000 for a fully automatic laddu making machine capable of producing 500+ kg per day.</strong> Whether you're opening a new mithai shop, upgrading an existing halwai business, or scaling up for festival-season demand, understanding the price landscape for laddu making machines, jalebi making machines, gulab jamun making machines, rasgulla making machines, barfi making machines, and kulfi making machines is critical to making a profitable investment. This comprehensive buyer's guide covers every machine type, price bracket, top manufacturer, and ROI calculation you need before purchasing sweet making equipment in India.</p>

    <p>India's mithai (sweet) industry is worth over ₹2,50,000 crore (2025 estimates) and growing at 15–18% annually. With rising labour costs, increasing FSSAI compliance requirements, and customer expectations for consistency, machine-made sweets are no longer a luxury — they are a competitive necessity. Traditional halwais who once relied entirely on manual skill are now investing in semi-automatic and fully automatic sweet making machines to boost production, maintain hygiene standards, and reduce dependency on skilled labour that is becoming harder and more expensive to find.</p>

    <p>Let's break down the complete pricing, specifications, and buying considerations for every major sweet making machine available in India.</p>

