    <h2>6. Kulfi Making Machine — Price, Types & Specifications</h2>
    <p>The <strong>kulfi making machine</strong> category covers both traditional mould-based setups and modern machine-based production. Kulfi — India's beloved frozen dairy dessert — is traditionally set in conical moulds submerged in ice-salt slurry or placed in freezers. Machines automate the filling, freezing, and demoulding steps.</p>

    <h3>Mould-Based Kulfi Making Setup (₹5,000 – ₹15,000)</h3>
    <p>The most basic approach uses stainless steel or aluminium kulfi moulds (matka shape, cone shape, or stick shape) filled manually and frozen. While technically not a "machine," this is how most kulfi vendors in India start.</p>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Mould set (50–100 pieces):</strong> ₹5,000 – ₹10,000</li>
      <li><strong>Kulfi filling stand:</strong> ₹2,000 – ₹5,000</li>
      <li><strong>Freezer required:</strong> Deep freezer (separate purchase — see <a href="/blog/fridge-for-shop-commercial-india">commercial fridge guide</a>)</li>
      <li><strong>Output:</strong> Depends on freezer capacity and batch cycle (typically 4–8 hours per batch)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Kulfi Making Machine / Kulfi Plant (₹15,000 – ₹80,000)</h3>
    <p>A kulfi making machine (sometimes called a kulfi plant) includes a mixing vessel with cooling jacket, automatic filling system, and rapid freezing unit. These machines reduce batch time from 4–8 hours to 1–2 hours and produce more consistent texture.</p>

