    <h3>How to Evaluate a Manufacturer</h3>
    <p>Before placing an order, always verify:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Factory visit:</strong> Visit the factory or at minimum request a video tour of the manufacturing facility</li>
      <li><strong>Material certificate:</strong> Ask for SS 304 material test certificates — some manufacturers use lower-grade steel and label it as 304</li>
      <li><strong>Client references:</strong> Speak with 2–3 existing customers in your city</li>
      <li><strong>Warranty terms:</strong> Standard is 1 year on motor, 6 months on parts — anything less is a red flag</li>
      <li><strong>After-sales service:</strong> Confirm response time for breakdowns and availability of spare parts</li>
      <li><strong>FSSAI compliance:</strong> Ensure machines meet FSSAI food-contact surface standards (see our <a href="/blog/fssai-license-cost-registration-india">FSSAI license guide</a>)</li>
    </ul>

