    <h4>Festival Season Multiplier</h4>
    <p>The real magic of machine investment shows during festival seasons. Diwali alone can account for 25–30% of a mithai shop's annual revenue. During Diwali week, demand can spike 5–10x normal levels. A shop with manual production simply cannot scale — they turn away orders. A shop with semi-auto or automatic machines can run double shifts and capture that demand. Many mithai shop owners report that a single Diwali season post-automation covers 60–80% of their entire machine investment.</p>

    <h2>11. How to Buy Sweet Making Machines — Step-by-Step Process</h2>
    <p>Follow this process to ensure you get the right machines at the best price:</p>

    <ol>
      <li><strong>Assess your product mix:</strong> List the sweets you plan to sell and their expected daily volumes. This determines which machines you need first.</li>
      <li><strong>Prioritize by ROI:</strong> Buy the machine for your highest-volume product first. For most shops, this is either a laddu making machine or a khoya machine.</li>
      <li><strong>Research manufacturers:</strong> Shortlist 3–4 manufacturers. Check reviews on IndiaMART, TradeIndia, and local food industry associations.</li>
      <li><strong>Request quotations:</strong> Get written quotes with specifications, GST breakup, delivery charges, and warranty terms.</li>
      <li><strong>Visit a factory or demo unit:</strong> Never buy a high-value machine without seeing it in operation. Most manufacturers welcome factory visits.</li>
      <li><strong>Negotiate:</strong> Prices are almost always negotiable. Buying multiple machines from one manufacturer typically gets you 5–15% discount.</li>
      <li><strong>Check power requirements:</strong> Confirm your shop's electrical supply matches the machine requirements (single-phase vs three-phase).</li>
      <li><strong>Plan the layout:</strong> Ensure your kitchen space can accommodate the machines with adequate clearance for operation and maintenance.</li>
      <li><strong>Arrange financing if needed:</strong> Explore <a href="/blog/bakery-equipment-financing">equipment financing options</a> — MSME loans, manufacturer EMI plans, or equipment leasing.</li>
      <li><strong>Confirm installation support:</strong> Most manufacturers provide free installation and training. Get this commitment in writing.</li>
    </ol>

